</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,1895,1992]" lastBlockId="3.[189,1399,265,361]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">
Females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Giroti &amp; Cotoras &amp; Lazo &amp; Brescovit, 2020" authorityName="Giroti &amp; Cotoras &amp; Lazo &amp; Brescovit" authorityYear="2020" box="[327,617,1895,1921]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="motumotirohiva" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,617,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Ariadna motumotirohiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[626,716,1895,1921]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1900" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[991,1348,1895,1921]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perkinsi">
<emphasis box="[991,1190,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Ariadna perkinsi</emphasis>
Simon, 1900
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Berland, 1933" authorityName="Berland" authorityYear="1933" box="[189,587,1930,1956]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lebronneci">
<emphasis box="[189,415,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Ariadna lebronneci</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Berland L." box="[422,587,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" pagination="39 - 70" refId="ref3864" refString="Berland L. 1933. Araignees des Iles Marquises. Bernice P. Bishop Museum Bulletin 114: 39 - 70." type="journal article" year="1933">Berland, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
due to the dark dorsal abdominal pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1169,1930,1956]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,798,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[189,1398,798,1843]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Ariadna motumotirohiva sp. nov., ♀, holotype (MNHN 8366). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Endites, labium and labrum, ventral view. D. Epigastric furrow, ventral view. E. Spinnerets, ventral view, arrowheads showing the diagonal membranous stripes of the ALS. F. Right leg I, prolateral view. G. Right leg I, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4240928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4240928/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Giroti A. M. &amp; Brescovit A. D." pageId="2" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref4448" refString="Giroti A. M. &amp; Brescovit A. D. 2018. The taxonomy of the American Ariadna Audouin (Araneae: Synspermiata: Segestriidae). Zootaxa 4400: 1 - 114. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4400.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Giroti &amp; Brescovit 2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 31a, e), but differ from the former by the anterior receptaculum with the dorsal lobe globous (
<figureCitation box="[198,270,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,776,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-162@4.[189,1398,776,1893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Ariadna motumotirohiva sp. nov., ♀, paratype (IBSP 246895). A–D. Internal genitalia. A, C. Lateral view, arrowhead in A = median membranous crack. B, D. Detail of the anterior receptaculum, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4240932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4240932/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Giroti A. M. &amp; Brescovit A. D." box="[281,575,265,291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref4448" refString="Giroti A. M. &amp; Brescovit A. D. 2018. The taxonomy of the American Ariadna Audouin (Araneae: Synspermiata: Segestriidae). Zootaxa 4400: 1 - 114. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4400.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Giroti &amp; Brescovit, 2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 31i–j), by the presence of three promarginal teeth on the chelicerae and femur IV with dorsal macrosetae, and from the latter by four promarginal teeth (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Berland L." pageId="3" pageNumber="100" pagination="39 - 70" refId="ref3864" refString="Berland L. 1933. Araignees des Iles Marquises. Bernice P. Bishop Museum Bulletin 114: 39 - 70." type="journal article" year="1933">Berland 1933: 44</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1–2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="100" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,324,401,427]" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="100">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="100" reason="3">
